s num\u00e9riques sont repr\u00e9sent\u00e9es par des points, des lignes et des surfaces.", "id": "003c603e-fda9-4ad3-a919-07c0d4a26129", "presentation_form": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\", \"coordinates\": [[[57.999994, -124.00000163], [57.9999938, -124.25000073], [57.9999958, -124.50001035], [57.9999916, -124.7500153], [57.9999994, -125.00000162], [57.9999916, -125.25000377], [57.9999954, -125.50000849], [57.999993, -125.74999983], [57.9999926, -126.00001429], [58.2499931, -126.00001423], [58.499995, -126.00000375], [58.7499995, -126.00001674], [58.9999969, -126.00000037], [58.9999961, -125.75001045], [58.9999976, -125.5000105], [58.9999924, -125.25001505], [58.9999986, -125.00000565], [58.99999, -124.75001369], [58.9999999, -124.50000268], [58.9999952, -124.2500048], [58.99999, -124.00000082], [58.7499941, -124.00000224], [58.4999947, -124.0000056], [58.2499948, -124.00001101], [57.999994, -124.00000163]]]}", "license_id": "", "resources": [{"url": "www.geogratis.gc.ca", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}, {"url": "www.geogratis.gc.ca", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}, {"url": "http://ftp2.cits.rncan.gc.ca/pub/bndt/250k_shp_en/094/k/bndt_094k_shp_en.zip", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "SHAPE"}, {"url": "ftp://ftp2.cits.rncan.gc.ca/pub/bndt/250k_shp_en/094/k/bndt_094k_shp_en.zip", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "SHAPE"}, {"url": "http://ftp2.cits.rncan.gc.ca/pub/bndt/250k_shp_fr/094/k/bndt_094k_shp_fr.zip", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "SHAPE"}, {"url": "ftp://ftp2.cits.rncan.gc.ca/pub/bndt/250k_shp_fr/094/k/bndt_094k_shp_fr.zip", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "SHAPE"}, {"url": "www.geogratis.gc.ca", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}], "browse_graphic_url": "http://www.fakeimageurl123.com/foo.jpg", "topic_category": "Imagery Base Maps Earth Cover  Imagerie carte de base couverture terrestre", "tags": [], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "2010-11-02", "time_period_coverage_start": "1960-01-01", "data_series_name": "National Topographic Data Base (NTDB)", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "1960-01-01", "notes": "The National Topographic Data Base (NTDB) comprises digital vector data sets that cover the entire Canadian landmass. Geomatics Canada has digitized and structured thousands of topographic maps, creating a complete and uniform product that can be highly useful in a broad range of industries. The NTDB includes features such as watercourses, urban areas, railways, roads, vegetation, and relief.The organizational unit for the NTDB is the National Topographic System (NTS), based on the North American Datum of 1983 (NAD83). Each file (data set) consists of one NTS unit at the 1:250,000 scale. The ground data is depicted through points, lines, and areas.", "title": "National Topographic Data Base (NTDB) - 094K", "keywords_fra": "Bndt-094k-2.4,Sciences de la terre,Utilisation - couverture des terres,Lacs,Altitude du relief,Couverture v\u00e9g\u00e9tale,B\u00e2timents,Rivi\u00e8res - cours d-eau,\u00c9lectricit\u00e9,Transport,Courbes,Pipelines,Communications,Aires d\u00e9sign\u00e9es,Chemin,Constructions,Relief et formes,Hydrographie,Hypsographie,Toponymie - noms de lieux,R\u00e9seau \u00e9lectrique,R\u00e9seau f\u00e9rroviaire,R\u00e9seau routier,Sols satur\u00e9s d-eau,V\u00e9g\u00e9tation,Colombie-britanique,Tuchodi lakes,094k", "organization": "nrcan-rncan", "department_number": "115"}
{"owner_org": "9391E0A2-9717-4755-B548-4499C21F917B", "data_series_issue_identification_fra": "2.0", "catalog_type": "Geo Data | G\u00e9o", "title_fra": "Matrices de correction de la BNDT - 065H09", "keywords": "Mat-corr-bndt-l7-065h09-1.2,Earth science,Infrastructure,Surface water,Topography,Vegetation,Nunavut,Ayotte lake,065h09", "data_series_issue_identification": "2.0", "ready_to_publish": "0", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "", "data_series_name_fra": "Matrices de correction de la BNDT", "spatial_representation_type": "Grid | Grille", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "As Needed | Au besoin", "author": "Natural Resources Canada | Ressources naturelles Canada", "author_email": "geoginfo@NRCan.gc.ca", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "Les matrices de correction de la Base nationale de donn\u00e9es topographiques (BNDT), aussi connu sous l'acronyme MATCOR, sont un produit d\u00e9riv\u00e9 du rehaussement planim\u00e9trique des jeux de donn\u00e9es de la BNDT \u00e0 l'\u00e9chelle de 1/50 000. La matrice de correction permet \u00e0 l'utilisateur d'am\u00e9liorer la pr\u00e9cision g\u00e9om\u00e9trique des donn\u00e9es moins pr\u00e9cises de la BNDT. La matrice est un ensemble de points r\u00e9partis sur une grille r\u00e9guli\u00e8re aux 100 m\u00e8tres, chaque point d\u00e9crivant les corrections planim\u00e9triques (DX, DY) \u00e0 apporter \u00e0 cet endroit. La position des points est en coordonn\u00e9es UTM (projection universelle transverse de Mercator) selon le syst\u00e8me de r\u00e9f\u00e9rence nord-am\u00e9ricain de 1983 (NAD83). Chaque fichier forme une zone rectangulaire recouvrant en son entier le jeu de donn\u00e9es de la BNDT associ\u00e9. Son d\u00e9coupage correspond donc grossi\u00e8rement au Syst\u00e8me national de r\u00e9f\u00e9rence cartographique (SNRC) \u00e0 l'\u00e9chelle de 1/50 000. Tous les jeux de donn\u00e9es de la BNDT \u00e0 l'\u00e9chelle de 1/50 000, dont la pr\u00e9cision originale est inf\u00e9rieure \u00e0 30 m\u00e8tres, devraient \u00eatre corrig\u00e9s g\u00e9om\u00e9triquement en utilisant des ortho-images Landsat comme r\u00e9f\u00e9rence spatiale. Le jeu de donn\u00e9es MATCOR contient une liste de coordonn\u00e9es et les corrections correspondantes \u00e0 appliquer sous la forme : X Y DX DY.", "id": "003c9490-d24c-48bd-a284-753a4dbd397b", "presentation_form": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\", \"coordinates\": [[[-96.5, 61.5], [-96.5, 61.75], [-96, 61.75], [-96, 61.5], [-96.5, 61.5]]]}", "license_id": "", "resources": [{"url": "www.geogratis.gc.ca", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}, {"url": "www.geogratis.gc.ca", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}, {"url": "http://ftp2.cits.rncan.gc.ca/pub/matcor/065/h/matcor_065h09.zip", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}, {"url": "ftp://ftp2.cits.rncan.gc.ca/pub/matcor/065/h/matcor_065h09.zip", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}, {"url": "www.geogratis.gc.ca", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}], "browse_graphic_url": "http://www.fakeimageurl123.com/foo.jpg", "topic_category": "Imagery Base Maps Earth Cover  Imagerie carte de base couverture terrestre", "tags": [], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "2010-11-02", "time_period_coverage_start": "2000-07-10", "data_series_name": "NTDB Correction Matrices", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "2000-07-10", "notes": "The correction matrices for the National Topographic Data Base (NTDB), also known under the acronym CORMAT, are products derived from the planimetric enhancement of NTDB data sets at the 1:50 000 scale. The correction matrix enables users to enhance the geometric accuracy of the less accurate NTDB. The matrix is a set of points arrayed on a regular 100-m grid. Each point describes the planimetric correction (DX, DY) to be applied at this location. The position of the points is given in UTM (Universal Transverse Mercator projection) coordinates based on the North American Datum of 1983 (NAD83). Each file constitutes a rectangular area covering the entire corresponding NTDB data set. Its delimitation corresponds more or less to National Topographic System (NTS) divisions at the 1:50 000 scale. All NTDB data sets at the 1:50 000 scale whose original accuracy was less than 30 m should be geometrically corrected by using the Landsat orthoimage as a spatial reference. A CORMAT data set contains a list of coordinates and the corresponding corrections to be applied in the form X Y DX DY.", "title": "NTDB Correction Matrices - 065H09", "keywords_fra": "Mat-corr-bndt-l7-065h09-1.2,Sciences de la terre,Infrastructure,Eau de surface,Topographie,V\u00e9g\u00e9tation,Nunavut,Ayotte lake,065h09", "organization": "nrcan-rncan", "department_number": "115"}
