{"owner_org": "9391E0A2-9717-4755-B548-4499C21F917B", "data_series_issue_identification_fra": "2.0", "catalog_type": "Geo Data | G\u00e9o", "title_fra": "Matrices de correction de la BNDT - 052N13", "keywords": "Mat-corr-bndt-l7-052n13-2.7,Earth science,Infrastructure,Surface water,Topography,Vegetation,Ontario,Berens lake,052n13", "data_series_issue_identification": "2.0", "ready_to_publish": "0", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "", "data_series_name_fra": "Matrices de correction de la BNDT", "spatial_representation_type": "Grid | Grille", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "As Needed | Au besoin", "author": "Natural Resources Canada | Ressources naturelles Canada", "author_email": "geoginfo@NRCan.gc.ca", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "Les matrices de correction de la Base nationale de donn\u00e9es topographiques (BNDT), aussi connu sous l'acronyme MATCOR, sont un produit d\u00e9riv\u00e9 du rehaussement planim\u00e9trique des jeux de donn\u00e9es de la BNDT \u00e0 l'\u00e9chelle de 1/50 000. La matrice de correction permet \u00e0 l'utilisateur d'am\u00e9liorer la pr\u00e9cision g\u00e9om\u00e9trique des donn\u00e9es moins pr\u00e9cises de la BNDT. La matrice est un ensemble de points r\u00e9partis sur une grille r\u00e9guli\u00e8re aux 100 m\u00e8tres, chaque point d\u00e9crivant les corrections planim\u00e9triques (DX, DY) \u00e0 apporter \u00e0 cet endroit. La position des points est en coordonn\u00e9es UTM (projection universelle transverse de Mercator) selon le syst\u00e8me de r\u00e9f\u00e9rence nord-am\u00e9ricain de 1983 (NAD83). Chaque fichier forme une zone rectangulaire recouvrant en son entier le jeu de donn\u00e9es de la BNDT associ\u00e9. Son d\u00e9coupage correspond donc grossi\u00e8rement au Syst\u00e8me national de r\u00e9f\u00e9rence cartographique (SNRC) \u00e0 l'\u00e9chelle de 1/50 000. Tous les jeux de donn\u00e9es de la BNDT \u00e0 l'\u00e9chelle de 1/50 000, dont la pr\u00e9cision originale est inf\u00e9rieure \u00e0 30 m\u00e8tres, devraient \u00eatre corrig\u00e9s g\u00e9om\u00e9triquement en utilisant des ortho-images Landsat comme r\u00e9f\u00e9rence spatiale. Le jeu de donn\u00e9es MATCOR contient une liste de coordonn\u00e9es et les corrections correspondantes \u00e0 appliquer sous la forme : X Y DX DY.", "id": "003f37df-2fd7-40d0-b095-8e6a53b30f06", "presentation_form": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\", \"coordinates\": [[[-94, 51.75], [-94, 52], [-93.5, 52], [-93.5, 51.75], [-94, 51.75]]]}", "license_id": "", "resources": [{"url": "www.geogratis.gc.ca", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}, {"url": "www.geogratis.gc.ca", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}, {"url": "http://ftp2.cits.rncan.gc.ca/pub/matcor/052/n/matcor_052n13.zip", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}, {"url": "ftp://ftp2.cits.rncan.gc.ca/pub/matcor/052/n/matcor_052n13.zip", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}, {"url": "www.geogratis.gc.ca", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}], "browse_graphic_url": "http://www.fakeimageurl123.com/foo.jpg", "topic_category": "Imagery Base Maps Earth Cover  Imagerie carte de base couverture terrestre", "tags": [], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "2010-11-02", "time_period_coverage_start": "2002-07-06", "data_series_name": "NTDB Correction Matrices", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "2002-07-06", "notes": "The correction matrices for the National Topographic Data Base (NTDB), also known under the acronym CORMAT, are products derived from the planimetric enhancement of NTDB data sets at the 1:50 000 scale. The correction matrix enables users to enhance the geometric accuracy of the less accurate NTDB. The matrix is a set of points arrayed on a regular 100-m grid. Each point describes the planimetric correction (DX, DY) to be applied at this location. The position of the points is given in UTM (Universal Transverse Mercator projection) coordinates based on the North American Datum of 1983 (NAD83). Each file constitutes a rectangular area covering the entire corresponding NTDB data set. Its delimitation corresponds more or less to National Topographic System (NTS) divisions at the 1:50 000 scale. All NTDB data sets at the 1:50 000 scale whose original accuracy was less than 30 m should be geometrically corrected by using the Landsat orthoimage as a spatial reference. A CORMAT data set contains a list of coordinates and the corresponding corrections to be applied in the form X Y DX DY.", "title": "NTDB Correction Matrices - 052N13", "keywords_fra": "Mat-corr-bndt-l7-052n13-2.7,Sciences de la terre,Infrastructure,Eau de surface,Topographie,V\u00e9g\u00e9tation,Ontario,Berens lake,052n13", "organization": "nrcan-rncan", "department_number": "115"}
{"owner_org": "9391E0A2-9717-4755-B548-4499C21F917B", "data_series_issue_identification_fra": "GEOBASE_1.0", "catalog_type": "Geo Data | G\u00e9o", "title_fra": "Donn\u00e9es num\u00e9riques d'\u00e9l\u00e9vation du Canada - 092O09", "keywords": "Cded-092o09-1.0,Earth science,Terrain elevation,Topographical relief,Contours,092o09,British columbia", "data_series_issue_identification": "GEOBASE_1.0", "ready_to_publish": "0", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "", "data_series_name_fra": "Donn\u00e9es num\u00e9riques d'\u00e9l\u00e9vation du Canada", "spatial_representation_type": "Grid | Grille", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "As Needed | Au besoin", "author": "Natural Resources Canada | Ressources naturelles Canada", "author_email": "SupportGeoBase@nrcan.gc.ca", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "Le Centre d'information topographique (CIT) produit les DNEC de concert avec des organismes f\u00e9d\u00e9raux, provinciaux et territoriaux ainsi qu'avec le secteur priv\u00e9.   Les DNEC consistent en un tableau ordonn\u00e9 de valeurs d'\u00e9l\u00e9vation au sol ou de surface (enregistr\u00e9es en m\u00e8tres) interpol\u00e9es \u00e0 des points r\u00e9guli\u00e8rement espac\u00e9s. Les donn\u00e9es sources num\u00e9riques des DNEC peuvent \u00eatre extraites des \u00e9l\u00e9ments hypsographiques et hydrographiques de la Base nationale de donn\u00e9es topographiques (BNDT) aux \u00e9chelles de 1/50 000 et 1/250 000, ou de la Base de donn\u00e9es g\u00e9ospatiales (BDG), ou de donn\u00e9es de position, \u00e0 diverses \u00e9chelles, acquises des provinces et territoires ou d'imageries de t\u00e9l\u00e9d\u00e9tection.", "id": "003f4efb-4ba2-4afa-8746-42ddd25e3600", "presentation_form": "Model Digital | Mod\u00e8le num\u00e9rique", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\", \"coordinates\": [[[-122.5, 51.5], [-122.5, 51.75], [-122, 51.75], [-122, 51.5], [-122.5, 51.5]]]}", "license_id": "", "resources": [{"url": "www.geobase.ca", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}, {"url": "www.geobase.ca", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}, {"url": "http://ftp2.cits.rncan.gc.ca/pub/geobase/official/cded/50k_dem/092/092o09.zip", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}, {"url": "ftp://ftp2.cits.rncan.gc.ca/pub/geobase/official/cded/50k_dem/092/092o09.zip", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}, {"url": "www.geobase.ca", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}], "browse_graphic_url": "http://www.fakeimageurl123.com/foo.jpg", "topic_category": "Elevation  \u00c9l\u00e9vation", "tags": [], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "2010-11-02", "time_period_coverage_start": "1998-08-28", "data_series_name": "Canadian Digital Elevation Data", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "1998-08-28", "notes": "The Centre for Topographic Information (CTI) jointly produces the CDED with federal, provincial and territorial government agencies as well as the private sector.   A CDED consists of an ordered array of ground or reflective surface elevations, recorded in metres, at regularly spaced intervals. The source digital data for CDED is extracted from the hypsographic and hydrographic elements of the National Topographic Data Base (NTDB) at scales of 1:50,000 and 1:250,000, or the Geospatial Data Base (GDB), or various scaled positional data acquired by the provinces and territories, or remotely sensed imagery.", "title": "Canadian Digital Elevation Data - 092O09", "keywords_fra": "Dnec-092o09-1.0,Sciences de la terre,Altitude du relief,Relief topographique,Courbes,092o09,Colombie-britanique", "organization": "nrcan-rncan", "department_number": "115"}
{"owner_org": "9391E0A2-9717-4755-B548-4499C21F917B", "data_series_issue_identification_fra": "Rapport n\u00b0 2, Direction g\u00e9n\u00e9rale des terres, Environnement Canada, 1972. u093n", "catalog_type": "Geo Data | G\u00e9o", "title_fra": "Inventaire des terres du Canada (1/250 000) - Possibilit\u00e9s des terres pour la faune - ongul\u00e9s - u093n", "keywords": "Animals,Game (wildlife),Soil,Ungulates,Soils,Soil compaction,Soil consistence,Soil fertility,Soil heat budget,Soil horizons - profile,Soil structure,Soil texture,Vegetation,Biomass,Indigenous vegetation,Land use - land cover,Land management", "data_series_issue_identification": "Report No.2, Lands Directorate, Environment Canada, 1972. u093n", "ready_to_publish": "0", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "", "data_series_name_fra": "Inventaire des terres du Canada (1/250 000) - Possibilit\u00e9s des terres pour la faune - ongul\u00e9s", "spatial_representation_type": "Vector | Vecteur", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "As Needed | Au besoin", "author": "Natural Resources Canada | Ressources naturelles Canada", "author_email": "geoginfo@NRCan.gc.ca", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "La cartographie des propri\u00e9t\u00e9s physiques des terres qui les rendent propres \u00e0 servir d'habitat aux ongul\u00e9s est \u00e9tablie dans le respect d'un syst\u00e8me national de classification \u00e9labor\u00e9 en collaboration avec le Service canadien de la faune et les organismes provinciaux de la faune. Comme les autres secteurs, le secteur des ongul\u00e9s pr\u00e9sente sept classes. Outre la classe et la sous-classe, le syst\u00e8me indique l'esp\u00e8ce d'ongul\u00e9s \u00e0 laquelle renvoie la classification. Pour assurer la reproduction, la survie et la croissance des ongul\u00e9s, une zone g\u00e9ographique donn\u00e9e doit receler leurs nutriments en quantit\u00e9 et en qualit\u00e9 suffisantes, leur habitat et leur espace requis en quantit\u00e9s n\u00e9cessaires.  La cartographie des possibilit\u00e9s des terres pour la faune se fonde sur l'interpr\u00e9tation de cartes a\u00e9riennes et des r\u00e9sultats d'\u00e9tudes effectu\u00e9es sur le terrain. Des cotes d'aptitude sont \u00e9galement \u00e9tablies en fonction du couvert v\u00e9g\u00e9tal optimum qui peut \u00eatre maintenu gr\u00e2ce \u00e0 de bonnes pratiques de gestion de la faune.", "id": "003fadbe-f842-5705-9e9d-69bb43bef65d", "presentation_form": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\", \"coordinates\": [[[-126, 55], [-126, 56], [-124, 56], [-124, 55], [-126, 55]]]}", "license_id": "", "resources": [{"url": "ftp://ftp2.cits.rncan.gc.ca/pub/geott/cli_250k/ungulate/u093n.shp.zip", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng", "format": "other"}], "browse_graphic_url": "http://www.fakeimageurl123.com/foo.jpg", "topic_category": "Biota  Biote", "tags": [], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "1972-01-01", "time_period_coverage_start": "", "data_series_name": "Canada Land Inventory (1:250,000) - Land Capability for Ungulates", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "", "notes": "The mapping of land capability for ungulates follows a national system developed with the aid of the Canadian Wildlife Service and the game branches of the provinces. The ungulate sector uses seven classes, like the others. In addition to class and subclass, the system indicates the ungulate species to which the classification refers. Capability for ungulate production implies a sufficient quantity and quality of food, protective cover, and space to meet the needs for survival, growth, and reproduction. Capability mapping is accomplished through interpretation of air photographs and by field surveys. Capability ratings are also established on the basis of the optimum vegetational stage that can be maintained with good wildlife management practices.", "title": "Canada Land Inventory (1:250,000) - Land Capability for Ungulates - u093n", "keywords_fra": "Animal,Gibier,Sol,Ongul\u00e9s,Sols,Compactage du sol,Consistance du sol,Fertilit\u00e9 du sol,Bilan thermique du sol,Horizons - profil du sol,Structure du sol,Texture du sol,V\u00e9g\u00e9tation,Biomasse,V\u00e9g\u00e9tation indig\u00e8ne,Utilisation - couverture des terres,Gestion des terres", "organization": "nrcan-rncan", "department_number": "115"}
